
@startuml

' Define classes
class Doctor {
    +practitionerNumber: String
    +fullName: String
    +address: String
    +phoneNumber: String
    +signature: Image
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class Patient {
    +healthNumber: String
    +firstName: String
    +lastName: String
    +dateOfBirth: Date
    +address: String
    +phoneNumber: String
    +appointments: List<Appointment>
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class Requisition {
    +validFrom: Date
    +tests: List<Test>
    +repetitionPattern: RepetitionPattern
    +repetitions: int
    +interval: Interval
    +doctor: Doctor
    +patient: Patient
    +results: List<TestResult>
}

class Test {
    +testType: String
    +duration: int
    +isWalkInOnly: boolean
    +isRepeatable: boolean
    +group: String
    +requisitions: List<Requisition>
}

class TestResult {
    +result: String
    +report: String
    +test: Test
    +requisition: Requisition
}

class Appointment {
    +confirmationNumber: String
    +date: Date
    +startTime: Time
    +endTime: Time
    +lab: Lab
    +requisition: Requisition
    +isCancelled: boolean
    +changeFeeApplied: boolean
}

class Lab {
    +registrationNumber: String
    +name: String
    +address: String
    +businessHours: BusinessHours
    +appointments: List<Appointment>
}

class RepetitionPattern {
    +pattern: String
}

class Interval {
    +intervalType: String
}

class BusinessHours {
    +openTime: Time
    +closeTime: Time
}

' Associations
Doctor --> "1..*" Requisition : prescribes
Patient --> "1..*" Requisition : receives
Requisition --> "1..*" Test : includes
Test --> "1..*" Requisition : part of
Requisition --> "1..*" TestResult : has
Test --> "1..*" TestResult : has
Patient --> "1..*" Appointment : makes
Requisition --> "0..1" Appointment : requires
Appointment --> Lab : at
Doctor --> "0..1" Doctor : can prescribe to (self)
Doctor --> "0..1" Doctor : can be prescribed by (self)

@enduml

---

### ✅ Notes:
- This class diagram captures all the entities and relationships described in the system requirements.
- It includes associations like `prescribes`, `receives`, `includes`, etc., as per the logic.
- Some helper classes like `RepetitionPattern`, `Interval`, and `BusinessHours` are included to model complex attributes.
- Relationships such as a doctor being able to prescribe to another doctor or themselves are modeled with self-associations.

